comments: Barrett (TOR) repeatedly exits the lane within three seconds when he is not actively guarding an opponent.
Although Barrett (TOR) makes contact with the ball with his left hand, he extends his right forearm into Christie's (LAL) left arm and initiates illegal contact during the shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) moves into Reaves' (LAL) path without establishing himself in a screening position and delivers illegal contact that affects his ability to defend.
Christie (LAL) moves alongside Barrett's (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Barrett (TOR) initiates illegal contact with Davis's (LAL) right wrist and causes him to lose control of the ball.
Reaves (LAL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Barnes' (TOR) shot attempt near the rim.
Davis (LAL) is moving alongside Barnes' (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs during his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) engages with Davis (LAL) as he moves off-ball and briefly grasps his arm, but does not affect his ability to receive the pass.
Siakam (TOR) lowers his arm across Davis's (LAL) right shoulder and initiates contact that affects his shot attempt.

Barrett (TOR) does not establish a legal screening position in Davis's (LAL) path, moving directly into him without giving him an opportunity to avoid the contact.  Davis's reaction was reviewed by senior league managers and determined to not meet the criteria for a postgame flopping violation because his movement is in the direction of his initial path given the contact.
Barnes (TOR) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
Siakam (TOR) commits a take foul on Reaves (LAL).
Christie (LAL) retreats away from Barnes (TOR) and when he jumps to contest the play at the basket, marginal contact occurs with Barnes' arm as he dunks the ball in.
As Barnes (TOR) reaches for the ball, he initiates illegal body contact with Davis (LAL) that causes him to lose his balance.
Barnes (TOR) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
